MANDATORY MODULES

The following modules are REQUIRED and binding:

MODULE: NON-COMMERCIAL USE ONLY

The Software may not be used for commercial purposes. "Commercial purposes" means:
- Any use primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage
- Any use by for-profit entities in their business operations
- Monetary compensation or financial gain
- Integration into commercial products or services

Permitted non-commercial uses include:
- Personal projects and individual use
- Academic and educational purposes
- Non-profit organizations with 501(c)(3) or equivalent status
- Open-source projects not generating revenue

---

MODULE: MILITARY AND DEFENSE PROHIBITION

The Software may not be used for military, defense, or national security purposes,
including but not limited to:
- Armed forces of any nation-state
- Defense contractors and military suppliers
- Intelligence agencies and security services
- Development of weapons, surveillance systems, or military technology
- Military training or simulation systems
- Any application supporting warfare, armed conflict, or military operations

---

MODULE: FOSSIL FUEL INDUSTRY PROHIBITION

The Software may not be used by or for the fossil fuel industry, including:
- Oil and gas exploration, extraction, production, or refining companies
- Coal mining operations and coal-fired power generation
- Organizations whose primary business involves fossil fuel activities
- Infrastructure for fossil fuel transportation, storage, or distribution
- Services directly supporting fossil fuel extraction or consumption

Exceptions: Renewable energy companies and organizations transitioning away from
fossil fuels may use the Software for non-fossil-fuel activities.

---

MODULE: DEMOCRATIC GOVERNANCE REQUIREMENT

The Software may not be used by governments that fail to meet democratic governance
standards as defined by internationally recognized metrics:

A government is considered non-democratic if it:

1. Scores below 6.0 on the Democracy Index published by The Economist Intelligence Unit
   (https://www.eiu.com/n/campaigns/democracy-index/)

2. Is classified as "Not Free" by Freedom House's Freedom in the World report
   (https://freedomhouse.org/report/freedom-world)

3. Is not recognized as an "Electoral Democracy" by Freedom House

4. Fails to meet the following minimum criteria:
   - Free and fair elections with universal suffrage
   - Peaceful transfer of power
   - Independent judiciary
   - Freedom of expression and press
   - Freedom of assembly and association
   - Rule of law and accountability mechanisms

Users representing government entities must verify their government's status using
the above criteria before using this Software.

---

MODULE: GENOCIDE AND COLONIALISM PROHIBITION

The Software may not be used by governments or entities that:

1. Are subject to genocide-related findings or proceedings:
   - Rulings or ongoing proceedings at the International Court of Justice (ICJ)
     regarding violations of the Genocide Convention
   - Determinations by the UN Human Rights Council of systematic human rights
     violations rising to the level of genocide or crimes against humanity
   - States designated under UN General Assembly resolutions as committing
     genocide or ethnic cleansing

2. Engage in ongoing colonization practices as defined by:
   - Occupation of territory not recognized by the United Nations
   - Settlements in occupied territories deemed illegal under international law
   - Administrative control over territories against the will of their inhabitants
   - Systematic displacement of indigenous or native populations
   - Denial of self-determination to peoples under their control

3. Are subject to EU sanctions or restrictive measures related to:
   - Serious human rights violations
   - Violations of international humanitarian law
   - Actions undermining territorial integrity or sovereignty
   - Destabilizing actions or policies

Current examples (as of January 2025, subject to updates):
- Israeli government entities (ICJ proceedings, occupation of Palestinian territories)
- Russian government entities (Ukraine invasion, EU sanctions)
- Myanmar military (Rohingya genocide findings)
- Any entity on the EU Consolidated Sanctions List

Reference sources:
- ICJ rulings: https://www.icj-cij.org/
- EU Sanctions Map: https://www.sanctionsmap.eu/
- UN Security Council Resolutions: https://www.un.org/securitycouncil/
- UN Human Rights Council: https://www.ohchr.org/en/hr-bodies/hrc/home

---

MODULE: UN SANCTIONS COMPLIANCE

The Software may not be used by entities subject to:
- UN Security Council sanctions
- UN Human Rights Council designations for serious violations
- International Criminal Court (ICC) arrest warrants or proceedings
- EU restrictive measures and sanctions
- Entities designated by international bodies for:
  * War crimes
  * Crimes against humanity
  * Terrorism
  * Human trafficking
  * Systematic human rights abuses

Users must verify compliance with:
- UN Security Council Consolidated List: https://www.un.org/securitycouncil/content/un-sc-consolidated-list
- EU Sanctions Map: https://www.sanctionsmap.eu/
- ICC Situations: https://www.icc-cpi.int/

---

UNIVERSAL DECLARATION OF HUMAN RIGHTS

In addition to the above modules, the Software may not be used to violate any
article of the United Nations Universal Declaration of Human Rights:
https://www.un.org/en/universal-declaration-human-rights/

This includes but is not limited to uses that:
- Violate dignity, equality, or human rights (Articles 1-2)
- Involve slavery, torture, or cruel treatment (Articles 4-5)
- Deny fair trial or legal rights (Articles 6-11)
- Violate privacy or enable surveillance abuse (Article 12)
- Restrict freedom of movement or assembly (Articles 13, 20)
- Deny freedom of thought, conscience, or expression (Articles 18-19)
- Undermine right to education, work, or social security (Articles 23-26)

---

VERIFICATION AND COMPLIANCE

1. Users must perform due diligence to verify compliance with these restrictions
2. Upon request, users must provide documentation demonstrating compliance
3. The licensor reserves the right to audit compliance and revoke permission for
   violations
4. Users must monitor changes to sanctions lists and democracy indices and cease
   use if they become non-compliant

---

UPDATES AND INTERPRETATION

The lists of prohibited entities and democracy metrics shall be understood to
update automatically as:
- New UN resolutions are passed
- ICJ rulings are issued
- EU sanctions are modified
- Democracy indices are updated annually
- New international findings on genocide or colonialism are made

Users are responsible for monitoring compliance with updated restrictions.

