---

DEFINITIONS

"Democratic government": A government scoring 6.0+ on Democracy Index AND
classified as "Free" or "Partly Free" by Freedom House, with free elections,
peaceful power transfer, independent judiciary, and protected civil liberties.

"Genocide": Acts defined in the UN Convention on the Prevention and Punishment
of the Crime of Genocide (1948).

"Colonization practices": Occupation, settlements, or administrative control
over territories not recognized by the UN, involving denial of self-determination.

"Commercial use": Any use primarily for commercial advantage or monetary
compensation, including by for-profit entities.

"Fossil fuel industry": Organizations whose primary business involves extraction,
processing, or distribution of oil, gas, or coal.

